Anunnaki 👽 part of a full sleeve I'm working on.
Thank you to Cameron for giving me free rein 🤘

In Mesopotamian mythology, the Anunnaki were a group of deities who played significant roles in the religious beliefs of the Sumerians, Akkadians, Babylonians, and Assyrians.
They were considered to be the offspring of Anu, the sky god, and his consort Ki, the earth goddess.
They were believed to have descended to Earth to establish civilization and exert control over humanity.
